body_html:
Apologies for the late reply, I was out.

DataType 23 corresponds to TF_UINT64:

tensorflow/tensorflow/core/framework/types.proto

Line 39 in ab0fcac

DT_UINT64 = 23;

support for which was added pretty recently (after TensorFlow 1.4 was cut) in commit 3bafe0a (see also #14331)

So the test at head will not work with the C library from the 1.4 branch.
You'll either need to run tests from the 1.4 branch or build the C library from head.

Please feel free to re-open if I misunderstood and you still see the problem at head (or when the Go code and C library versions are inconsistent)

body:
Apologies for the late reply, I was out.

DataType 23 corresponds to `TF_UINT64`:

https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/ab0fcaceda001825654424bf18e8a8e0f8d39df2/tensorflow/core/framework/types.proto#L39

support for which was added pretty recently (after TensorFlow 1.4 was cut) in commit https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/3bafe0a86f67dd54197c6d60bdb5053f510de7d8 (see also #14331)

So the test at head will not work with the C library from the 1.4 branch.
You'll either need to run tests from the 1.4 branch or build the C library from head.

Please feel free to re-open if I misunderstood and you still see the problem at head (or when the Go code and C library versions are inconsistent)
